#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/pivot_point/bounding_box_center.rst:14
msgid ""
"The bounding box is a rectangular box that is wrapped as tightly as "
"possible around the selection. It is oriented parallel to the world axes."
" In this mode the pivot point lies at the center of the bounding box. You"
" can set the pivot point to bounding box with :kbd:`Comma` or via the "
"menu in the editor's header. The image below shows how the Object's "
"Bounding Box size is determined by the size of the Object."
msgstr ""

